# Load shapley values
load("./data/rdata_files/shapley_values_fdis_999.RData")
shapley_values_fdis <- shapley_values

VARImp

var_imp_fdis <-
     autoplot(shapley_values_fdis) +
               theme_bw() +
               ylab("") +
               xlab("Variable Importance") +
               theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
                    axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
                    axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
                    axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))
autoplot(shapley_values_fdis, type = "contribution", num_features = 13) +
          theme_bw() +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))

Explain

shap_long_fdis <-
     as.data.frame(shapley_values_fdis) %>%
          tibble::rownames_to_column("plot") %>%
          pivot_longer(!plot,
                         names_to = "variable",
                         values_to = "shap_value") %>%

        # Change predictors'names
        mutate(variable = case_when(
                    variable == "sand" ~ "Soil Sand %",
                    variable == "limo" ~ "Soil Limo %",
                    variable == "p_h" ~ "Soil pH",
                    variable == "acidity" ~ "Soil acidity",
                    variable == "ca" ~ "Soil Ca Concentration",
                    variable == "mg" ~ "Soil Mg Concentration",
                    variable == "k" ~ "Soil K Concentration",
                    variable == "p" ~ "Soil P Concentration",
                    variable == "organic_matter" ~ "Soil Organic Matter",
                    variable == "elev" ~ "Plot elevation",
                    variable == "slope_per" ~ "Plot Slope %",
                    variable == "prec" ~ "Mean annual precipitation",
                    variable == "temp" ~ "Mean annual temperature",
               TRUE ~ variable))
fdis_shap  <-
     ggplot(data = shap_long_fdis, aes(x = variable, y = shap_value, color = shap_value)) +
               geom_point(show.legend = FALSE) +
               viridis::scale_colour_viridis(option = "inferno") +
               coord_flip() +
               theme_minimal() +
               geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed",
                     color = "#9d9d9d", linewidth = 1) +
               ylab("") +
               xlab("") +
               theme(legend.position = "none",
                    axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
                    axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
                    axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
                    axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25)) +
               geom_jitter(aes(colour = shap_value), width = 0.2)

shap_long_redundancy <-
     as.data.frame(shapley_values_redundancy) %>%
          tibble::rownames_to_column("plot") %>%
          pivot_longer(!plot,
                         names_to = "variable",
                         values_to = "shap_value_redun")  %>%

                  # Change predictors'names
          mutate(variable = case_when(
                    variable == "sand" ~ "Soil Sand %",
                    variable == "limo" ~ "Soil Limo %",
                    variable == "p_h" ~ "Soil pH",
                    variable == "acidity" ~ "Soil acidity",
                    variable == "ca" ~ "Soil Ca Concentration",
                    variable == "mg" ~ "Soil Mg Concentration",
                    variable == "k" ~ "Soil K Concentration",
                    variable == "p" ~ "Soil P Concentration",
                    variable == "organic_matter" ~ "Soil Organic Matter",
                    variable == "elev" ~ "Plot elevation",
                    variable == "slope_per" ~ "Plot Slope %",
                    variable == "prec" ~ "Mean annual precipitation",
                    variable == "temp" ~ "Mean annual temperature",
               TRUE ~ variable))
redundancy_shap <-
     ggplot(data = shap_long_redundancy, aes(x = variable, y = shap_value_redun,
                                             color = shap_value_redun)) +
               geom_point() +
               viridis::scale_colour_viridis("Shapley Value", option = "inferno") +
               coord_flip() +
               theme_minimal() +
               geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed",
                     color = "#9d9d9d", linewidth = 1) +
               ylab("") +
               xlab("") +
               theme(legend.position = c(0.9,0.2),
                    axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
                    axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
                    axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
                    #axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
                    axis.text.y = element_blank()) +
               geom_jitter(aes(colour = shap_value_redun), width = 0.2)
